 not the core utility until a method is called. It seems to return null because the class isn't instantiated yet. The `ErrorHandler` requires `OptionConverter`, which isn’t loaded until referenced. I think the missing dependency is causing issues for the logging level as well. The threshold is null likely due to changes in the source code. I'm considering if the runtime jar has altered, affecting method verification on the JVM.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing NoClassDef issues**\\n\\nI'm trying to pinpoint when the `NoClassDef` error occurs, likely during method invocation. The `convertArg` function references `OptionConverter` in the `ErrorHandler` branch, but it may not apply to the `Level` branch. This results in a failure, leading to null values. It seems that `setProperties` now requires the core dependency, so adding `log4j-core` could be necessary. The main classes identified in the source explicitly include `PropertySetter`, which could explain the missing `OptionConverter` class error.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ITq3jl9O3vKxK5zvozFtcwsG|fc_0d8c5ba1daecb9c8016a0104ae8e708195b0a19fd921885b3e", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.logging.log4j/log4j-1.2-api/2.18.0/gradle.properties"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4195, "output": 927, "cacheRead": 46592, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 51714, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778451614699, "responseId": "resp_0d8c5ba1daecb9c8016a0104a09ee48195a19619ad95af7be7"}}
